A serial 'prankster' claims he was arrested at Buckingham Palace after posting videos of himself openly taunting the Queen's security guards.

The self-proclaimed 'crazy dangerous prankster', who says his name is Michael Blunt, has become a YouTube sensation with his footage which shows him tormenting the armed guards.

The videos also include the usually straight-faced guards' reactions to his filming - which sometimes including pointing their bayonets towards the camera.

